        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-01-07 07:02:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nI got a good remark from Sylvain...even if it is a \"light\" patch, you should get used to a better formalism especially in the title and do not be shock by the -1 / -2 ...\n99.9% of the cases all the votes are here to help the patch submitter not to judge him/her.\n\nWhen submitting a patch , the title shall be fully explicit for the reviewers..\nhere we understand that it is to learn how to submit a patch but we do not have any information on the content of the patch\n\nOOM and 1 integration repo are using a regex to force the title formalism, the main integration not for the moment\nI would recommend\n\n[domain] description\nso here\n\n[Documentation] Main README refactoring\n\ncould you amend your patch to change the title..",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
